      <narrative xml:lang="EN">2019
1.     No public education and awareness on the Vigilante Act, 2019 (Act 999); 
2.	Lack of public knowledge on the Roadmap and the Code of Conduct for the eradication of vigilantism in Ghana
3.	107 hotspots in all the 16 regions of Ghana

2020
1.	25% of Constituency Executives of all the seven major political parties in Ghana aware of and activating the provisions in Act 999 and the Roadmap for eradicating Vigilantism
2.	30% of Police District Commanders&#x2019; knowledge enhanced on the Vigilante law and the Roadmap
3.	The number of hotspots in 2020 reduced by 30%</narrative>
